    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at this contract for a freelance gig and i don't really get what this 'indemnification' part means. it sounds kinda scary. can u explain it in simple terms?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Indemnification, in simple terms, is like having a shield against the bad stuff, or more accurately, a promise that someone will cover the costs if something goes wrong. It's a clause where one party agrees to protect the other party from financial loss or legal trouble. Think of it like this: if a problem arises because of something you did (or didn't do) in the contract, you have to step up and cover the damage. It's a big, heavy piece of the deal, so you really need to know what kind of things you're agreeing to cover.",
